Gemini: no changes added to commit (use "git add" and/or "git commit -a")
This means:

The merge was successful in bringing the changes from temp-orphan into your main branch. These are the files that were changed or added by the merge.
However, these changes are not yet saved in a commit. They are currently in your "working directory" and "staging area" but need to be finalized with a commit.
To finish the merge, you need to commit these changes.

Here's what you should do:

Stage all the changed files:

C:\ai-execution-system>git add .
This command tells Git to add all the modified files (listed in git status) to the "staging area". Think of the staging area as preparing these changes to be included in your next commit.

Commit the staged changes:

C:\ai-execution-system>git commit
Since you already wrote a commit message in the notepad during the merge, Git might reuse that message. If it opens the notepad again, just save and close it (it will likely have your previous message). If it doesn't open the notepad, it means it used the message from earlier.

After you run these two commands, the changes will be committed to your main branch, and the merge will be fully completed.

After committing, run git status again to confirm that your working directory is clean (it should say "nothing to commit, working tree clean").
